        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 17 at 7:24AM CDT by NWS Quad Cities IA IL</headline>
        <description>At 723 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Le Claire, or near Bettendorf, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fulton, Portland Corners, Rapids City, Folletts, Spring Hill, Erie,
Garden Plain, East Clinton, Port Byron, Newton Corners, Albany, Rock
Creek Marina and Campground, Barstow, Hillsdale, Princeton, Le
Claire, Illiniwek Forest Preserve, Clinton, Princeton Wildlife Area,
and Camanche.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 80 in Iowa between mile markers 303 and 306.
Interstate 80 in Illinois between mile markers 1 and 5.
Interstate 88 between mile markers 1 and 23.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
